⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Chris
node CPS · CPS · ⟦Chris:CPS:86a32c⟧

WHO   — Chris — the watchful outsider
WHAT  — A figure outside the family's frame: the kind of marginal, observing presence the film uses to throw its suburban dread into relief.
WHERE — CPS · Crime + Punishment in Suburbia  Framework inputs: Crime + Punishment in Suburbia (2000)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a story of suburban not-seeing needs a witness from outside it — someone the comfortable world overlooks.
HOW   — By standing apart, watching, and seeing what the suburb trains itself not to.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I live where the suburb doesn't look — which is the only place you can see it clearly.

